RBC Capital Markets Hires Detwiler, Milcetic and Weiner for U.S.

-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-03-03T18:08:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/rbc-capital-markets-hires-detwiler-milcetic-and-weiner-for-u-s-.html
  RBC Capital Markets  said it hired
investment bankers Bill Detwiler, Paul Milcetic and P.A. Weiner
as managing directors to expand its U.S. investment banking
business.  Detwiler, who was hired from Royal Bank of Scotland Group
Plc, will help lead RBC’s communications, media and
entertainment business, the firm said today in an e-mailed
statement. Detwiler, who has 17 years experience in the media
area, also worked at  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)  and Deutsche Bank AG.  Milcetic, who has 20 years experience including a decade at  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN) , will lead RBC’s chemicals team and work
within the metals and mining group, the Toronto-based firm said.  Weiner, who has more than two decades experience including
15 years at Deutsche Bank, will lead RBC’s technology
investment-banking group’s practice in financial technology and
transaction processing.  RBC is the investment banking unit of  Royal Bank of Canada (RY) ,
the country’s largest bank by assets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
